Does pageNum have to compared first? If and only if pageNum doesn&#39;t match should you compare freeSpace? Then I suggest changing the code like this, which reflects that logic:

    bool operator&lt;(const PageMeta&amp; pm) const {
		return pageNum &lt; pm.pageNum || (pageNum == pm.pageNum &amp;&amp; freeSpace &lt; pm.freeSpace);
    }

It all depends on the ordering you want to impose. Does pageNum take precedence over freeSpace or vice versa? You need to decide and change your &lt; operator to make the comparison correctly. Check the logic of comparing the members and the order in which they are compared is right.

